---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact WattCostGuide"
  description="Contact WattCostGuide for appliance wattage corrections, calculator feedback, methodology questions, and site suggestions."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <h1>Contact</h1>
    <p>Send calculator corrections, wattage suggestions, article ideas, or general questions.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section two-column">
    <div class="article-block">
      <h2>What to include</h2>
      <p>
        If you are suggesting a correction, include the appliance name, model if available, wattage source,
        and the page URL. Clear source details make updates much easier to verify.
      </p>
      <p>
        For calculator feedback, include the values you entered for watts, hours, and electricity rate, along
        with what result you expected. This helps us reproduce the estimate and check whether the page copy
        needs clarification.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-panel">
      <h2>Email</h2>
      <p><a href="mailto:hello@wattcostguide.com">hello@wattcostguide.com</a></p>
      <p>We review practical corrections and appliance suggestions for future site updates.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Editorial corrections</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide is built around transparent formulas and practical wattage ranges. If a page lists a
      wattage range that seems too high, too low, or unclear for a common appliance type, send the source and
      we will review it for a future update.
    </p>
    <p>
      We cannot provide utility billing advice for a specific account, but we can improve calculator examples,
      clarify formulas, and update educational explanations when better information is available.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
